      <div class="row" style= "padding: 4%">
        <p>UVC Tech was developed in response to the emerging issues around student health in dormitories and student
          housing as they can become a cesspool for infectious disease in the winter months. Although the technology was initially developed for
          student housing, there are numerous markets that would benefit from the implementation of UV-C-LED Anti-Bacterial technologies.
          If made an industry standard in health care facilities, UV-C-LED Anti-Bacterial technologies will significantly decrease the likelihood
          of invasive infections in all health care facilities while also limiting the use of harmful cleaning chemicals.
          Many UVC Tech Anti-Bacterial technologies use LED’s to emit UV-C light to break the chemical bonds in the surface bacteria
           to eliminate surface transfers. The Liquid Silicone Rubber on the surface of the cover is of medical grade to ensure superior quality. We
